<BaseLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description} canonicalUrl={frontmatter.canonicalUrl}>
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href={frontmatter.url} />
  <link rel="alternate" hreflang="zh" href={frontmatter.zhUrl} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

  <article class="tutorial-article">
    <header class="tutorial-header">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/providers/">Providers</a> / <a href="/providers/aliyun/">Alibaba Cloud Bailian</a> / Review
      </div>
      <h1>Alibaba Cloud Bailian API Review: Qwen Models Pricing & Experience in China</h1>
      <div class="meta">
        <span>By APIRank</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <time datetime="2026-05-17">May 17, 2026</time>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>Review</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="ad-slot ad-top"></div>

    <div class="content-body">
      <section>
        <p class="lead">China-based development teams face a fundamental challenge that international developers rarely consider: most leading AI APIs are either blocked, throttled, or painfully slow from mainland China. OpenAI's API requires proxy infrastructure. Anthropic's Claude is inaccessible without a VPN. Google Gemini shows intermittent connectivity. For teams building products inside China, this isn't just an inconvenience — it's a dealbreaker that can invalidate an entire technical architecture.</p>

        <p>Alibaba Cloud's <strong>Bailian</strong> (百炼, meaning "Hundred Forges") platform emerges as a compelling domestic alternative. Built around the Qwen family of models developed by Alibaba's DAMO Academy, Bailian promises direct access, competitive pricing, and tight integration with Alibaba Cloud's broader ecosystem.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Alibaba Cloud Bailian Overview</h2>
        <p><strong>Bailian</strong> (百炼) is Alibaba Cloud's unified AI development platform, positioned as a one-stop shop for model access, fine-tuning, and enterprise AI solutions. The platform centers on the <strong>Qwen</strong> model series — Alibaba's flagship open-weight language models that have gained significant traction in the Chinese developer community.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Supported Models on Bailian</h2>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Context Window</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>qwen-max</strong></td><td>32K</td><td>Most capable Qwen model; best for complex reasoning</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>qwen-plus</strong></td><td>128K</td><td>Balanced performance and cost; most popular</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>qwen-turbo</strong></td><td>32K</td><td>Fast inference; optimized for latency-sensitive use cases</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>qwen-vl-plus</strong></td><td>32K</td><td>Vision-language model for image understanding</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p>The <strong>qwen-plus</strong> model with its 128K context window stands out in the domestic model landscape. Only Moonshot Kimi's 128K model offers comparable context length among Chinese providers.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Pricing Breakdown</h2>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Input Price</th><th>Output Price</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>qwen-max</td><td>¥0.12 / 1K tokens</td><td>¥0.60 / 1K tokens</td></tr>
              <tr><td>qwen-plus</td><td>¥0.04 / 1K tokens</td><td>¥0.12 / 1K tokens</td></tr>
              <tr><td>qwen-turbo</td><td>¥0.004 / 1K tokens</td><td>¥0.012 / 1K tokens</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p><strong>qwen-turbo</strong> at ¥0.004 input / ¥0.012 output per 1K tokens is remarkably cheap — among the lowest-priced LLM APIs available in China.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Key Advantages of Alibaba Cloud Bailian</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Fast domestic access</strong> — no proxy, no VPN required within China</li>
          <li><strong>Extremely competitive pricing</strong> — qwen-turbo at ¥0.004/1K input undercuts most competitors</li>
          <li><strong>128K context window</strong> — qwen-plus supports up to 128K tokens for long document processing</li>
          <li><strong>Generous free tier</strong> — no credit card required to start</li>
          <li><strong>Alibaba Cloud ecosystem integration</strong> — seamless with OSS, Function Compute, and other Alibaba Cloud services</li>
          <li><strong>Fine-tuning support</strong> — LoRA fine-tuning available for qwen-turbo and qwen-plus</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Limitations and Concerns</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Model capability gap</strong> — Qwen models trail GPT-4 and Claude on complex reasoning and coding tasks</li>
          <li><strong>Smaller ecosystem</strong> — fewer integrations and tools compared to OpenAI's ecosystem</li>
          <li><strong>Documentation usability</strong> — less intuitive than OpenAI's developer documentation</li>
          <li><strong>International access limited</strong> — Bailian is primarily optimized for China-based users</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Budget Analysis: Tokens Per $100</h2>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>$100 buys (input)</th><th>$100 buys (output)</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>qwen-turbo</td><td>~180M tokens</td><td>~59M tokens</td></tr>
              <tr><td>qwen-plus</td><td>~18M tokens</td><td>~5.9M tokens</td></tr>
              <tr><td>qwen-max</td><td>~5.9M tokens</td><td>~1.2M tokens</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p>qwen-turbo delivers extraordinary value at scale — $100 buys approximately 180 million input tokens, making it ideal for high-volume applications.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Use Case Recommendations</h2>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Use Case</th><th>Recommended Model</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>High-volume cost-sensitive apps</td><td>qwen-turbo (¥0.004/1K)</td><td>Lowest cost, fast inference</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Long document analysis</td><td>qwen-plus (128K)</td><td>128K context handles full documents</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Complex reasoning tasks</td><td>qwen-max</td><td>Most capable Qwen model</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Image understanding</td><td>qwen-vl-plus</td><td>Vision-language capabilities</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Already in Alibaba Cloud</td><td>Any Bailian model</td><td>Native ecosystem integration</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <details>
            <summary><strong>Q: Do I need an Alibaba Cloud account to use Bailian?</strong></summary>
            <p>Yes. Bailian is accessed through Alibaba Cloud's console. You'll need an Alibaba Cloud account billed through your subscription. Domestic accounts require identity verification, though international cards are accepted for payment.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary><strong>Q: How does Bailian's qwen-plus compare to GPT-4o-mini on cost?</strong></summary>
            <p>qwen-plus at ¥0.04/1K input (~$0.0056/1K) is significantly cheaper than GPT-4o-mini at $0.15/1K input — approximately 27x cheaper on input costs. Capability comparisons are context-dependent; GPT-4o-mini outperforms on coding and complex reasoning.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary><strong>Q: Can I fine-tune Qwen models on Bailian?</strong></summary>
            <p>Yes. Bailian provides fine-tuning pipelines for qwen-turbo and qwen-plus, supporting LoRA fine-tuning with custom datasets stored in Alibaba Cloud OSS. Fine-tuning costs are separate from inference costs.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>Alibaba Cloud Bailian occupies a strategically valuable position in China's AI API landscape: direct, low-latency access to competitive Qwen models at aggressive price points, wrapped in Alibaba Cloud's enterprise infrastructure. The combination of 128K context on qwen-plus, generous free tier, and ¥0.004/1K pricing on qwen-turbo makes Bailian particularly well-suited for high-volume applications, long-document workflows, and teams already embedded in the Alibaba Cloud ecosystem.</p>
        <p><strong>Ready to get started?</strong> Visit <a href="https://bailian.console.aliyun.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alibaba Cloud Bailian Console</a> to create your account and start building with Qwen models today.</p>
        <p><em>Compare Bailian with other providers on <a href="/providers/aliyun/">APIRank</a> — real-time pricing, availability in China, and user reviews.</em></p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="ad-slot ad-bottom"></div>

    <aside class="sidebar">
